caption: Absolutely stunning place. In the summer, all the flowers are blooming and you can vote for your favourite rose tree. From June-July, the Chopin Festival runs and I highly recommend you to attend a candlelit concert in this park. Bring your own water as it gets hot.  Beautiful gardens and parks and there are even peacocks who live here. Great place for photography or just to have a picnic.
Lovely place for roses and peacocks

The Orangery is part of the Park or Garden of Bagatelle, it is a pretty space and the setting is even more beautiful, the gardens of Bagatelle are enchanting, the trees are majestic, there are streams, waterfalls , kiosks, there is also the Rose Garden, it is so big and beautiful that as soon as you leave you want to go back. Incredible works by Monet with his now informal long water lilies and a collection full of works from the 19th century to the mid-20th century. Some important works from Picasso's pink period are exhibited here.
